{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Review input is scoped to changed lines only, not full modified files.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: failure is typically at module handoff (diff parser -> review-input builder), not single-function logic. REAL-INFRA/LLM-DEP/MULTI-STEP: none required. Candidate tests: (Integration) setup PR-diff fixture with unchanged buggy lines + changed clean lines, run diff-to-review-input pipeline, assert only changed hunks are sent; catches leaking full-file context from wiring bugs. (Unit) setup isolated line-filter function, assert it filters correctly; misses bugs where upstream module passes full file blob. Rejection-gate: rejected System because behavior text only requires scoping of input content, not real network/OS/API semantics.","test_description":"Run modules that ingest diff payload and construct model input using stubbed PR data; assert serialized review input contains only changed hunks/line ranges and excludes unchanged file regions.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.32,"Integration":0.58,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Inline comments attach to correct diff positions on the pull request.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"REAL-INFRA + MOCK-HIDE: GitHub diff-position semantics are external API behavior; mocks often accept invalid mappings that real PR API rejects or misplaces. Candidate tests: (System) setup real test PR/commit, post inline comments with computed positions, assert comments appear on intended diff lines; catches position-vs-line mapping errors. (Integration) setup mocked review API, assert request payload fields; misses real API interpretation failures. Rejection-gate: rejected Integration because behavior text is explicitly about 'correct positions in the diff view on the pull request' (real platform rendering/semantics).","test_description":"Against a real GitHub test PR, compute positions from diff hunks, post inline comments via API, then fetch review comments and verify each maps to intended file + diff line.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.12,"System":0.8,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"Agent finds at least one real defect in a PR containing a known introduced bug.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"LLM-DEP: correctness depends on model judgment about defect presence; deterministic stubs always pass and cannot validate detection quality. Candidate tests: (Agentic) setup real bug-seeded PR diff, run real model analysis, assert >=1 finding matches expected defect class/location tolerance; catches model misses. (Integration) setup fixed mock model response containing defect, assert pipeline accepts it; misses true detection failure. Rejection-gate: rejected Workflow because behavior text requires one detection outcome, not multi-agent decision chain.","test_description":"Run analyzer with real model on a curated PR containing a known bug; assert at least one produced finding correctly identifies that bug (by file/region/category).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.76,"Workflow":0.12}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"Each top-level summary finding maps to an inline comment ID from the same run.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: failure is cross-module state consistency (inline-post results -> summary assembler). No real OS/network/model output needed if IDs are stubbed deterministically. Candidate tests: (Integration) setup orchestrator with fake comment-poster returning run-scoped IDs, build summary, assert every summary item references an emitted ID from current run; catches stale-cache/cross-run mixups. (Unit) setup pure formatter function, assert field presence; misses orchestration state leakage. Rejection-gate: rejected System because behavior text is about same-run ID linkage, not external API behavior.","test_description":"Execute posting+summary composition modules together with deterministic stubs and run-id context; assert summary ID set is exactly a subset of IDs returned by inline-post step for that run.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.26,"Integration":0.64,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"No inline finding is dropped from summary payload before posting.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is pipeline handoff/aggregation (finder list -> summary payload), not model quality or OS behavior. Candidate tests: (Integration) setup multi-finding inline result set through orchestrator path to summary payload builder, assert payload count/content preserves all findings; catches truncation/filtering bugs between modules. (Unit) setup single payload-builder function with ideal input, assert mapping; misses drops caused by queue/state transitions before builder. Rejection-gate: rejected System because behavior text targets pre-post payload completeness, which can be validated with in-process wiring.","test_description":"Run end-to-end in-process orchestration from collected inline findings to summary payload creation (with poster stub); assert one-to-one preservation of finding identifiers.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.34,"Integration":0.58,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"Sequence (read diff, post inline, post summary) succeeds on a real PR with fixed precomputed findings.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"REAL-INFRA: requires real PR API calls and sequencing against external service; fixed findings remove LLM dependency. Candidate tests: (System) setup real test PR + fixed findings fixture, execute full posting sequence, assert all API calls succeed and artifacts visible; catches auth/rate-limit/payload/ordering failures. (Integration) setup mocked GitHub client, assert call order and payload shape; misses real API constraints and failure modes. Rejection-gate: rejected Agentic because behavior text says 'fixed precomputed finding set' (no model judgment needed).","test_description":"Run automation against a real GitHub sandbox PR using deterministic findings input; verify diff fetch, inline comment creation, and final summary comment all complete without manual steps.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.87,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"Full live run with model-generated findings completes correctly on a real PR without manual intervention.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"Combines real model decision(s) plus downstream real API actions in one end-to-end pipeline; failures can arise in agentic output -> posting handoff and sequential orchestration. Candidate tests: (Workflow) setup real PR, run full autonomous pipeline (read/analyze/post inline/post summary), assert completion + consistency between generated findings and posted artifacts; catches cross-step agentic orchestration failures. (Agentic) setup analyze-only real model test, assert findings quality; misses execution/posting/handoff breakdowns. Rejection-gate: rejected lower Agentic because behavior text explicitly requires full sequence completion for a real PR, not just model analysis output.","test_description":"Execute the production pipeline end-to-end on a real sandbox PR with live model inference enabled; assert run terminates successfully, inline comments are posted, and summary reflects posted findings with no manual correction.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.03,"System":0.14,"Agentic":0.27,"Workflow":0.56}}]}
